            Imagine securing an art gallery with the fewest guards possible. This is the essence of the Art Gallery Problem, a classic puzzle in computational geometry that challenges us to find the optimal way to cover a space. It&#039;s all about achieving maximum visibility with minimum resources. Our goal for this session is to unravel this problem together, from its initial setup to its surprising and intuitive solution.


